file_content.text: Calling all forces: these ancient ruins contain incredible technologies, but the Imperials are trying to drive us out and seize the ruins for themselves.
They've activated a security system built into the ruins that could destroy us all. It's powered by two energy pylons. Archaeologist Jorn can explain.
Once the system is fully charged, it will open a kind of portal just outside our camp. If that portal opens... I believe it'll mean disaster.
It is possible to redirect the system's energy and open a portal near the Empire's camp instead--just capture and synchronize the energy pylons.
But be careful: every time the pylons are activated and synced up, they'll emit a powerful explosive discharge.
Attention, all forces! The Empire must capture the ancient technologies contained within these ruins before the Republic can claim them.
Out of desperation, our enemies have activated the ruins' security system, powered by two energy pylons. Major Tull will explain.
As soon as the system reaches its full charge, it will open a portal outside our camp. From what we've deciphered, that means disaster.
Fortunately, we can redirect the system's energy and open a portal outside the Republic camp instead--if we capture and synchronize the energy pylons.
But be warned: each time the pylons activate and sync up, they will unleash a powerful explosive discharge.
This training exercise simulates the ancient ruins of the planet Seline. Your objective is to capture them before the enemy can.
The ruins contain a powerful security system, which is charged by two energy pylons nearby.
Once the system is fully charged, it will open a portal outside your camp, and your team will be eliminated.
Luckily, you can make the system open a portal outside the enemy team's camp instead--just capture and synchronize the energy pylons.
But be careful: every time the pylons are activated and synchronized, they fire off a powerful explosive discharge.
We've created this replica of the ancient Seline ruins for training purposes. The objective is to capture them before the opposing team can.
The scenario revolves around the ruins' ancient security system, which is powered by two energy pylons nearby.
Once the system reaches full charge, it opens a portal outside your camp, eliminating your team instantly.
To win, you must redirect the system to open a portal outside the enemy team's camp instead, by capturing and synchronizing the energy pylons.
However, the system is dangerous: every time the pylons are locked down, they emit a deadly explosive discharge.
